== Description ==

The '''BIM Nudge Down''' command moves the selected objects down (negative y direction) on the current working plane by the configured nudge distance.

See [[BIM_Nudge|BIM Nudge]] for general information about nudge tools, including how to configure the nudge distance.

== Usage ==

# Select one or more objects in the [[3D_view|3D View]].
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the '''Manage → Nudge → ''' '''Down''' option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut {KEY|N} {KEY|Down}.
# The selected objects are moved/rotated by the configured nudge distance.

